Once upon a time there lived a rabbit and a tortoise. They decided to have a race one day. 
When the race started, the rabbit quickly ran, reaching near the finishing line quickly, while
the tortoise started slowly.
The rabbit felt confident he would win against such a slow opponent. So, he casually took a nap
near the finishing line thinking the tortoise would not be able to cross him.
Yet, the tortoise kept walking at a slow, but consistent and steady pace. Soon